review.reviewBody:
We bought this item two years ago and it is a dream.  We keep all our kitchen gear in it and there is room to spare. We could probably shove everything into two of the storage bags and use the bottom compartment, unzipped, to store the camp stove. We leave the table top in place so we can use the pocket for longer items like spatulas and tongs that won&apos;t  fit in the gear bags.  I love that the camp kitchen is modular, so everything is convenient; no digging through plastic bins.  I&apos;ve seen people go to great lengths to build camp kitchens like a cabinet maker, but this is smaller, lighter, and just as durable.  

Assembly out of the box is not too bad, and sometimes one of the legs resists sliding (a little dry lube should keep that working).  

When my brother and his wife joined me for the eclipse and saw how I had my site set up, they said, &quot;Let&apos;s just get whatever he has.&quot;
